As of the [[2020 United States census|census of 2020]],<ref name="2020-census-5556700">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census: New Glarus village, Wisconsin |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?g=1600000US5556700&y=2020&d=DEC%20Redistricting%20Data%20%28PL%2094-171%29 |website=data.census.gov |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |access-date=July 31, 2022}}</ref> the population was 2,266. The [[population density]] was {{convert|1,261.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 1,014 housing units at an average density of {{convert|564.3|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the village was 94.0% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.6% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.6% [[Black (U.S. Census)|Black]] or [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.1% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.6% from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 4.1% from two or more races. Ethnically, the population was 2.9% [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race. The most reported ancestries were:<ref>{{cite web |title=TOTAL POPULATION |url=https://data.census.gov/table?t=-06:-1000E:-3000F:-4000G:-5000K:-7000E:-8000B&g=160XX00US5556700&d=DEC+Detailed+Demographic+and+Housing+Characteristics+File+A |website=data.census.gov |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref>
